{
  "stem": "10181.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But to go back to the school part, they started-- the law came that we had to-- no longer could go to school after a certain date.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So I remember the last day in school, you know, I remember the teacher being very unhappy about it, the Dutch teacher.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he said, I'm sorry that you have to go-- leave.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "You always were good students, and-- and I hope you-- everything is going to be OK.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And then they had all-- there was a Jewish school which was organized in a town which was about 15 kilometers away called [?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Dueterhum. ?] It was a bigger town where all the little villages-- a lot of little villages in the area, and they all had a Jewish population.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we all went to this school in [?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Dueterhum. ?]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "How did we go?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The first five or six kilometer were by horse and cart, because a bus didn't come into our village anymore.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then we took this-- then we went to what was called the main road.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Then we took one of those buses, which I explained before with those smoking things at the back and then took it to [?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Dueterhum. ?]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that was-- it was a whole day thing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "By the time we got back, it was in the evening.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The horse and cart waited for us at-- at the-- in a-- in a town called-- it wasn't a town, it was like a spot, called [?",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Bontebok. ?] That-- it still exists.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that's like a crossroads, and that's where they were used to wait for us-- the horse and cart-- and take us back to home.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was about six or eight kids who went on that little horse and cart.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Then also, we had to start wearing the Jewish star in 1942.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I thought around June, July '42, I think it was.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "This was mandatory.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "If you-- the threat was if they caught you without a Jewish star, you were immediately taken to a concentration camp, to a labor camp.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was in Dutch.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Jood was written on it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Jood means Jew.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It was six-- you know, the Jewish star, six-- in yellow-- yellow with black letters.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I didn't really-- forgot to tell you.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One of the things which the Germans did at the very beginning after the invasion of Holland was-- looked very innocent.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They made everybody register, have an identity card, OK?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now this is a very innocent thing, but what-- what did they do if you were Jewish, you had to put-- they put a big J on your identity card.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And of course, the Dutch Civil Service, which continued to function, did not-- did not resign-- maybe some people resigned.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Jews, of course, were thrown out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But this Dutch Civil Service continued to function under the direction of the Germans, you know, as if nothing had happened, and they give out identity cards.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and some people realized-- well, maybe people didn't even realize at the time what it meant, you know.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But right away you were separated because you were the only one who had a different identity card.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "This is how they separated you, OK?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And this was done, very easy for them, you know, because at the beginning, I guess, except for very few-- there might have been a few people who were smart who managed to maybe find a way of not getting the identity card, but I've never come across anybody but there could have been.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I imagine most people didn't.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Especially, as you went to your local registrar who knew you, so he wasn't gonna put-- if you were Jewish, he wasn't going to say no.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They just functioned under the orders of the Germans as if nothing had happened.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this is how they could identify you.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they-- if they had suspicion, they would ask for your identity card, and-- and if you had Jew on it and you didn't wear the star, and it was just too bad for you.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that's how they-- that was the next step.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now you said that they were-- threatened to take you to the camps.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What-- what were you hearing about camps?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's very strange what I heard, because the only camp I heard of-- and this was-- the threat, was a camp called Mauthausen.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was in Austria.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Apparently-- how did I hear about it?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because apparently in Amsterdam, they had rounded up in the ghetto that there was-- the Jews were ghettoized in Amsterdam.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was a general strike in 1941 over about three days of the dockworkers, and-- and some working-- you know, workers strike, and there was a sort of riot in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
